1
00:00:00,952 --> 00:00:03,476
See! Here we have a little phantom.

2
00:00:05,658 --> 00:00:07,207
What are you doing, Yato?

3
00:00:07,254 --> 00:00:09,384
Good! We want that reaction.

4
00:00:09,479 --> 00:00:12,236
Hate and fear will help you draw a borderline.

5
00:00:12,444 --> 00:00:13,460
And what's that?

6
00:00:13,485 --> 00:00:18,418
A borderline is what serves as a
regalia's shield. It's also his only weapon.

7
00:00:18,443 --> 00:00:21,373
Now, then. You did some pretty nice work the other day.

8
00:00:21,532 --> 00:00:22,929
I think you're ready for this.

9
00:00:23,104 --> 00:00:25,800
Humph! Flattery won't get you anywhere.

10
00:00:26,848 --> 00:00:29,260
It's real simple. Make your fingers into a halberd.

11
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:32,910
Then use them to draw a line like this between you and it.

12
00:00:34,702 --> 00:00:36,321
Uh, okay.

13
00:00:39,178 --> 00:00:40,188
Here goes!

14
00:00:42,687 --> 00:00:45,369
Amazing! So that's what you were talking about?

15
00:00:45,841 --> 00:00:51,533
Yep. Useful stuff. Phantoms can't cross it. It
acts as a boundary between "self" and "other."

16
00:00:51,787 --> 00:00:55,715
Is it something you can do, too? Or-or even me?

17
00:00:55,938 --> 00:00:59,923
No. You and I can't do this.
Borderlines are a regalia power.

18
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,680
Any regalia should be able to make one.

19
00:01:03,664 --> 00:01:06,476
But creating one that's this strong without practice...

20
00:01:07,199 --> 00:01:10,628
I've never known a regalia
who could do that. It's a first.

21
00:01:12,199 --> 00:01:14,866
Speaking of the Regalias that he knows...

22
00:01:19,157 --> 00:01:24,490
So, um. That girl we ran into down by
the water. Nora? She's a regalia, too?

23
00:01:24,807 --> 00:01:26,675
Oh, Nora, huh?

24
00:01:27,930 --> 00:01:29,037
How to put it...

25
00:01:31,815 --> 00:01:34,294
I guess you could call her a friend with benefits.

26
00:01:35,048 --> 00:01:35,680
Eh...

27
00:03:06,643 --> 00:03:09,342
I've decided that I'm going to look after Yukine.

28
00:03:09,445 --> 00:03:10,175
Huh?

29
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:15,283
You are? That's crazy. He can't
stay with you. It would never work.

30
00:03:15,308 --> 00:03:17,941
It makes more sense for him to stay with me than with you.

31
00:03:17,966 --> 00:03:21,657
