when you swiped some of my dad's drinks from the fridge?

167
00:13:46,978 --> 00:13:51,833
No, it's not like that. The pain
only goes in one direction, you see.

168
00:13:51,927 --> 00:13:56,320
From regalia to master, which actually
makes sense, if you think about it.

169
00:13:56,907 --> 00:14:02,788
After all, Regalias used to be people.
And people sin. Some more than others.

170
00:14:10,218 --> 00:14:17,310
Resentment, fear, envy, desperation, sadness, greed.

171
00:14:18,537 --> 00:14:23,055
Those emotions tempt Regalias to
do what they otherwise might not.

172
00:14:23,517 --> 00:14:30,650
Acting on them brings pain. We gods feel that pain,
and from it we learn something of what it is to be human.

173
00:14:31,575 --> 00:14:35,343
Listen, Hiyori. I think there are
some things I ought to clear up for you.

174
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:42,536
People decide what's right and wrong, but those
concepts don't apply to gods. To put it in simple terms,

175
